Mexican Stocks: Grupo Mexico, Mexichem, OHL Mexico Advance

-- B y   K a t i a   P o r z e c a n s k i
-- 
2011-09-27T22:07:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/mexican-stocks-grupo-mexico-industrias-penoles-mexichem-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 1.2 percent to 33,783.68.  Grupo Mexico  SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, gained 3.6 percent to 33.82 pesos. Copper, lead
and zinc jumped on speculation European policy makers will
intensify efforts to contain the region’s debt crisis.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM* MM), the largest maker of plastic
pipes in  Latin America , rose 1.2 percent to 43.60 pesos. Shares
have gained 5.1 percent over the last two days. Mexichem owns
plants in  South America  and the U.S.  OHL Mexico SA (OHLMEX* MM) soared a record 7.4 percent to
21.22 pesos. The local unit of Spanish construction company
Obrascon Huarte Lain SA joined the benchmark IPC index at the
start of this month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Porzecanski in New York at 
 kporzecansk1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
